Apologies, I thought I had reported every issue we could find, but looks like some of these weren't covered by yesterdays reports. We now only have 10 / 3100 components that can't be migrated by the schematic, so we are really close! üòÑ 

Input:
```
<ng-container
  *ngIf="true; then template"
></ng-container>
<ng-template #template>
  Hello!
</ng-template>
```

Error thrown (output remains the same):
> *ngIf: TypeError: Cannot read properties of null (reading '0')

Expected output:
```
@if (true) {
  Hello!
} 
```

